{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d04cd300-cb2d-41f5-a5c9-78e2aee41dbc","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — run tests with hot reload, re-running on file changes\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only execute tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. If you want an exact match instead, use `=` with the fully qualified name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ffb91a68-01fa-4888-abdb-21e4f1e71a56","outputTokens":144,"requestId":"6804:2D5697:18161BD:1B274E2:69FD427D"},"id":"854ff5c8-f00c-41cc-9d5f-5e039683109e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:55:14.629Z","parentId":"6b84bba4-38f9-47db-883f-d57c66159dc3"}
